      "HOW TO BUILD A CHROME EXTENSION BUSINESS WITH AI (my workflow)\n\nGo to any major platform and ask: what's this website missing?\n\nLook for:\n\n– What's annoying users?\n– What's repetitive and manual?\n– What features are hidden?\n– What do power users hack together?\n\nThe biggest websites have millions of users but can't build every feature. LinkedIn can't add every sales tool. YouTube can't add every analytics feature. Amazon can't add every shopping helper.\n\nThat's your opening.\n\nVidIQ built YouTube analytics and has millions of users. Grammarly built writing assistance and sold for $13B. Honey built coupon finding and sold for $4B.\n\nWhy Chrome extensions work:\n\nDistribution is built-in. You're not convincing people to visit a new website or download an app. You're adding features to sites they already use daily.\n\nThe users are already there. The behavior is already established. You're just making their existing workflow better. You piggyback off them (read their terms and services too to make sure it wont bug them)\n\nMost successful extensions follow the freemium model: basic features free, advanced features $5-15/month.\n\nSome go one-time purchase: $20-50 for lifetime access.\n\nOthers do usage-based: $0.10 per action, which scales with value.\n\nHOW TO BUILD MVP\n\nIt's crazy but you can literally ask Claude/ChatGPT/etc to build you a Chrome Extension now\n\n1. Tell Claude: \"Build me a Chrome extension that automatically saves LinkedIn profiles to a Google Sheet when I visit them.\"\n\nIt'll write the entire codebase. Manifest file, content scripts, background scripts everything.\n\n2. Have Bolt/Lovable create a marketing site. Funnels with Perspective or Clickfunnels.\n\n3. Ask ChatGPT to add features: \"Now add a button to categorize contacts as 'hot lead' or 'cold lead.'\"\n\n4. Use Cursor to debug and iterate. The AI handles the technical stuff while you focus on solving the actual problem.\n\n5. You can hire someone to help scale it and with security as revenue comes in. (important step)\n\nFun business to be building If you can get it right. Hope this got your creative juices flowing.\n\nHappy building!\n\n(for startup ideas, check out ideabrowser.com)",
