      "The most dangerous skillset combo right now: builder (designer or engineer) + filmmaker.\n\nYou're a 1 person factory from creation to distribution.\n\nThink about it. Most companies have two massive cost centers: building the product and marketing it. They hire engineers, designers, then pay agencies or marketing teams to create content that sells what they built.\n\nYou skip all of that.\n\nYou design the app, code it, then film the demo videos that make it go viral. No middlemen. No agency markups. No explaining your vision to someone else who has to translate it.\n\nThe speed advantage is insane. While competitors are coordinating between teams, you're shipping.\n\nThe cost advantage is obvious. You're not paying $50k/month to agencies.\n\nBut the real edge to be honest is the dividends you get from authenticity. When the person who built the product is also telling its story, the message hits different. You understand every detail because you created every detail.\n\nMost founders either build well or market well. The ones who do both become impossible to compete with.\n\nThey're vertically integrated humans in a world of fragmented teams.\n\nAnd when people talk about the $1B solo founder, this is the skillset they'll have.\n\nThey won't just code. They won't just create content.\n\nThey'll be the person who builds the future and films it happening.\n\nAnd for startup ideas you can steal, steal them at ideabrowser.com",
