      "We wrapped up a record June at Unify. We closed $1M of new ARR in a single month for the first time ever. We also:\n \n(1) Accelerated ARR growth to 17% m/m\n(2) Announced Unify for Sales Reps\n(3) Moved out of both our NYC and SF offices\n \n--\nDouble clicking into each of these:\n \n(1) Accelerated ARR growth to 17% m/m\n \nWe've been investing a ton of energy to revamp and level up how we sell. We tightened our ICP and re-focused around closing great fit customers. We onboarded Hassan to lead RevOps and Gregg as a sales advisor. We've leveled up our enablement, coaching and training. All of these are the inputs to revenue growth.\n \nI'm insanely proud of our whole go-to-market team for a record month.\n \n(2) Unify for Sales Reps\n \nYesterday we put out the biggest product release in Unify's history. We're doubling down on what makes Unify unique - data and workflow in a single platform, and one that's as easy for reps to use as it is for growth teams. With this release, we're re-inventing the sales engagement category.\n \n(3) Moved out of NYC and SF offices\n \nWe've scaled to 47 team members across SF and NYC and with it we're moving into new offices. 353 Sacramento in SF and 665 Broadway in NYC. More to share on these new spaces soon.\n \nAt this scale, I'm fully in editor mode now. My job has evolved from doing the work myself to holding the quality bar and connecting the dots between the right people.\n \nSometimes you need to take one step back to take two steps forward. June was a two steps forward month 📈",
