      "Today, I'm thrilled to share an article by OpenAI on our collaboration to engineer growth. And we've got a massive product launch to go alongside it: the Unify Observation Model powered by OpenAI's o3.\n \nIt's been 2 years since OpenAI Startup Fund first invested in Unify. From Day 1 of our journey, Connor and I were drawn to work with OpenAI because it felt clear to us that AI would be the biggest technology shift of our lifetimes.\n \nDespite the release of many amazing products in 2023 and 2024, it's felt like we’ve been living in a world of AI 1.0. A world where AI is helpful, but still isn’t deeply intelligent in the way a human is. This is especially true in GTM tech.\n\nWe can all feel that AI 2.0 is coming, and we’re excited to usher in this new agentic era at Unify. Today, we're taking another step in that direction, with the launch of Unify's Observation Model, powered by OpenAI's o3 model.\n \nAs of today, Unify can now learn, research, and remember like a human seller does.\n \nOur Observation Model runs 24/7, monitoring companies in your TAM to identify high-signal events (new hires, funding rounds, stack changes) through multi-agent workflows that understand context, rather than keywords.\n \nIt understands your relationships with your prospects and customers like a human seller does. It has a flexible memory that regularly updates as new insights are gathered or interactions happen. \n \nTLDR: The Observation Model feels more like a human brain than anything we’ve shipped before.\n \nIf you're curious about the details, I'll leave the link to the full story in the comments 👇 Also, drop me a note if you want a demo.",
