    imgUrl: "",
    postContent:
      "This might get me into some fights with AI SDR companies, but I don't care. Billboards across SF are filled with AI SDR companies saying \"Stop hiring humans\" or \"The era of AI SDR is here.\" I couldn't disagree with this take more.\n\nThe constant debate about AI is whether it's replacing humans or augmenting labor. But both of these schools of thought miss the point: you're selling to a human on the other side of the table.\n\nThat human will buy your product, and then another human at their company will have to deploy it and use it on a regular cadence. So even if AI takes away work that humans used to do, someone still needs to manage it, optimize it, and make decisions about it.\n\nPeople are so stuck on the AI debate that they forget that all software replaces work that humans historically did. Humans just evolved the work that they did. And found better things to spend their time on.\n\nThis is why we're still hiring humans at Unify instead of replacing team members with AI. Because there will always be things AI can't replace, like:\n\n(1) Cold calls: Using AI for this is illegal. Plus the best cold callers are 100x better than AI.\n(2) Relationship building: AI can't read between the lines, build genuine rapport, or pick up on the subtle buying signals that humans naturally catch in conversations.\n(3) Meet people in person: if I could replace all my zoom meetings with coffee chats I'd do it in a heart beat. People naturally agree more in person.\n\nYes, AI helps us scale outbound, but humans are what make the entire go-to-market engine actually work.\n\nI don't care if this burns any bridges with AI SDR companies. Those billboards are selling a fantasy.",
