      "Today is day 878 of Unify. If I could give myself one piece of advice on day 1, it'd be to invest in top-of-funnel (automated outbound, social) 6 months earlier than we did.\n \nComing out of 2023, the fundraising environment was rough. The fundraising market was in a hangover coming out of 2021 and 2022.\n \nSo we tried to be extremely efficient and lean as a company. We were conservative about every hire and every dollar we spent – which was fantastic for keeping burn low. But as a result, we underinvested in top-of-funnel ideas early on.\n \nIn retrospect I think this was a missed opportunity. Here's what I would have done differently:\n(1) Start posting 5 days per week on Linkedin a year earlier than I did\n(2) Hire 2 BDRs immediately after finishing our design partner program\n(3) Start our automated outbound program with Unify at the same time\n \nAutomated outbound generated $7M in pipeline for us in 2024. And social content drove 19% of our inbound pipeline. This could be even higher had we started earlier.\n \nIn the early days, over-invest in top-of-funnel to maximize learnings.\n \nP.S. thanks to Pascal for having me on the focal podcast to talk about our founding journey 🙌 I'll leave a link in the comments for the full episode.",
