    postContent:
      "In Q1 we improved our monthly gross retention by 5% by deeply focusing on ICP.\n \nHere's what we learned:\n \nFor our first 12 months of selling, we closed any deal we could get, as most startups do. We were selling to 5-person startups and 1,000+ employee companies, and everyone in between. Growth was great, pipeline was strong.\n \nBut then churn started to pick up. \n \nWe realized that for companies who don't have product-market-fit, we were struggling to get them to consistent meetings booked.\n \nIn Q1 of this year we had to take our medicine and tighten up our ICP. As a founder, that trade-off can be tough - it hurt to watch fewer deals come in. But it ultimately paid off:\n \n(1) Our new customer ACV is up +101% since December\n(2) Monthly gross retention has improved by 5% since February\n(3) We've 4x'ed the number of $100k+ ARR customers we have\n \nWhat I've learned is that investing behind ICP is something we need to be continuously doing. Even when we take a bet to go broader, be intentional about what this will do to your ICP and be aware of the risks.\n \nBy narrowing focus on ICP, we were able to dramatically improve customer health in just 3-6 months.",
