      "We use Attention to continuously learn from 500-1000 sales calls per month. My top focus is on making Unify an AI-first company. Attention is a huge piece of that, and helps us level up sales and product development.\n \nInstead of tracking competitive intel by spending hours listening to every call recording and taking notes, anytime a prospect mentions our competitors on a call, our entire team can listen into how the rep handled the situation.\n \nHow this works:\n(1) Attention records all sales calls\n(2) AI extracts the exact context of what prospects said, this is based on a custom prompt\n(3) A workflow in Attention sends an instant Slack alert to sales + product\n(4) We include a snippet of the conversation so we can hear the context around the mention\n \nToday it's possible for product and sales to know everything that's being mentioned on sales calls. In 2025 every business needs to be AI-first.",
