      "My unfiltered predictions on the (not-so-distant) future of martech...\nBased on observations from MKT1's Typeform survey of 200+ marketers.\n\n🧩 Enrichment, workflow builders, and AI layers will be in every tool you use. This is quickly becoming table stakes, not a differentiator.\n\n🫥 Your source-of-truth data won’t live front and center in a CRM—it’ll quietly power everything behind the scenes.\n\n🧃 As channels evolve, so do the tools. We’re seeing consolidation and a changing of the guard across inbound, outbound, lifecycle, events, and ecosystem marketing.\n\n🪚 It’s time to be a builder and a creative. New tools = fewer limitations. Carpe diem, marketers.\n\n🧟‍♂️ Legacy tools are falling behind. What once felt modern now feels clunky, especially in CRMs and website builders.\n\n🧬 Marketing productivity = adaptability. It’s not about the best PM tool. It’s about building the stack that gets you there.\n\n--\n\nAgree, disagree, got any other predictions to add to the list?\n\n⬇️ For a longer list and survey results, today's newsletter has it all. We also launch a new GTM Tool Library. \n\nThanks to Typeform, 42 Agency, and Caspian Studios for partnering with us to make this survey and newsletter happen.",
