      "I still see companies sleeping on a tactic in 2025 that I’ve been championing for 15 years...\nIt’s visual data storytelling.\n\nI’ve been bullish on marrying design and data since my Ticketfly days in 2012, here’s proof:\n\n🎫 We made a Ticketfly infographic with proprietary EDM ticket sale data, which became our most popular piece of content and was covered on all the music industry blogs of the day.\n(We even hired an infographic designer—different era!)\n\n💰 At Carta, we launched a study on the gender equity gap, which was featured in 50+ publications, and later we even had a billboard with this data.\n\n🖼️ I guess it tracks that I now run a newsletter that is arguably more known for its diagrams and visual storytelling than the writing.\n\nSo a reminder: invest in great data storytelling. \n\nIn a world of AI-generated content where standing out requires original insights, doing proprietary research, using aggregated and anonymized data, and adding visuals that tell your story instantly is an amazing way to stand out.\n\nI’d love to see some of your favorite b2b data visualizations, especially if they are throwbacks from the 2010s!\n—\nProof that data reports are hot right now: Canva's new data report on… data reports.\n\nA few stats that stood out, with my reactions\n• 66% of marketers feel anxious working with data (time to get over it!)\n• Only 44% feel confident starting data-heavy tasks (you got this! AI helps)\n• 88% say visuals make their work more credible (Canva makes this easy!)\n\nThe report is worth a read ⬇️\nhttps://lnkd.in/e9JjRZcM\n\n#designedwithcanva #canvapartner",
