    postContent:
      "How to get your marketing team to adopt AI in one day...Run a Marketing AI Hackathon.\n\nI just wrote a whole newsletter on how to do this, which was inspired by:\n1️⃣  The way Clay runs hackathons with their customers. \n\u003E They get teams to adopt custom signals, workflows, etc and get comfortable in the tool in one day\n\n2️⃣ The internal company-wide hackathons we did quarterly when I was at Asana. \n\u003E Intentional moments of scrappy building made a huge impact on both culture and shipping quick, fun wins (like the Asana Yeti)\n\n3️⃣ By AI adoption teams have faced over the past couple of years.\n\u003E Most marketing teams are just scratching the surface on  how to actually use AI (beyond content generation) consistently.\n--\nSo here’s how to run an internal Marketing AI Hackathon:\n✅ Pick a day and make it mandatory\nPut it on the calendar and treat it like a real team ritual. Mid-quarter is usually a sweet spot, or try it at an offsite. One hackathon is good, a quarterly cadence is better.\n\n✅ Set constraints and pick tools\nAvoid blank-page paralysis by giving the team 1–2 constraints: one tool, one use case, or internal-only projects. Share a short list of approved tools. We like Clay, Lovable, Replit, Retool, Canva, Gamma, Figma Make, and more.\n\n✅ Kick off with a short brainstorm\nStart the day with a quick meeting to review the format, goals, tools, and demo timing. Then give the team 15–30 minutes to jam on ideas and form teams.\n\n✅ Build something real in a day\nKeep the scope small. Encourage scrappy builds over perfection...whether it’s an internal tool, content generator, or signal-based campaigns\n\n✅ Demo, celebrate, and roll it forward\nSchedule demos the next day. Maybe even give out fun awards. Pick 1–3 projects to turn into real workflows or templates. AI adoption starts here and it sticks when you actually use what you build.\n\n---\nMy latest MKT1 newsletter includes:\n➡️ 70+ hackathon ideas and AI prompts\n➡️ Examples from Clay’s customer hackathons\n➡️ Details on what we built during our very own MKT1 Hackathon\n\nHave you tried something like this with your team? Or another method to get everyone adopting AI?\n\nThanks to our sponsors for this newsletter: Sendoso, Sequel.io, and Omni Lab",
