    type: "Image",
    postContent:
      "Teach a course → Build a community → Earn customers\n\nThis is the flywheel GC AI used to get from Seed to Series A super fast.\n\nGC AI provides an AI-powered platform for in-house legal teams, they just raised a Series A and are growing like crazy. (Full disclosure: I'm an investor)\n\nHere’s how their flywheel works:\n🧩 Founder-market-fit: Cofounder is Cecilia Ziniti, is a former GC at companies including Replit, who’s been experimenting with AI long before most legal teams were even thinking about it.\n\n1️⃣ Community and education before product: Before launching the company, Ceclilia started teaching Maven courses to help in-house lawyers learn about AI\n \n📈  Courses as acquisition: After launching the product, she kept teaching. The courses still focus on how legal teams can use AI, now with GC AI naturally introduced as part of the solution.\n \n🆓 Built-in trial: Students get a free trial of GC AI get hands-on experience with the product \n\n👯  Ongoing community: Every course cohort joins a Slack group, helping each other adopt AI (and GC.ai). Many of these community members know each other from being in the same cohort.\n\n🎈 Land & expand: The course taker becomes the internal champion, who already  knows the founder and trusts the product.\n\n🎟️ Referrals: Students recommend the course (and tool) to other GCs. The flywheel...flywheels\n\n--\n\nHere’s why I love this:\n🚀 Leveraging their founder-market fit marketing advantage: Cecilia is the expert and the face of the brand. Teaching scales trust better than 1:1 sales.\n\n🎓 Market education: GC AI has cracked the code on how to educate their audience about the problem and the potential solutions—and actually generating demand\n\n🌕 GC AI has found not only a lever to drive acquisition, but also to drive community.\n\n---\nThis is a great example of ecosystem marketing and community at work. And why I believe ecosystem marketing is the next big growth lever.\n\nDoes your company do anything like this? \n\nIf I can find more examples maybe a course as an acquisition channel newsletter is needed.",
