    postContent:
      'Is the company blog dead? Is that even the right question? Are you sick of people declaring marketing things "dead" on LinkedIn?\n\nWe covered all of this in our lightning round on the latest episode of Dear Marketers Podcast and newsletter, here\'s the summary:\n\n❓ Is the company blog dead? \n🎙️ Not completely. But with SEO fading as the primary way to “distribute” blog content and LLMs able to generate basic blog content quickly, it’s definitely not alive and kicking.\n\n❓Should you replace your blog with a resource center? \n🎙️Call this part of your website whatever you want, but either way you should likely be making actual resources not just written content for audience. "Vibe marketing" and "vibe coding" with AI make this easier.\n\n❓Is there still a place for long-form content in this new world? \n🎙️ Absolutely. But it needs to be in the right format, make use of expertise, have a stand-out POV, and proper distribution.\n\n❓Should you host your company blog on Substack? \n🎙️ Maybe for individual experts, but company Substacks usually don’t work. The loss of control doesn’t make up for the distribution gains.\n\n❓Should you build a blog for LLMs, not humans? \n🎙️ Think about the LLMs, but don’t forget the humans. Focus on your long-term strategy: writing with a strong and memorable point of view.',
