    postContent:
      "10 learnings from my first 24h creating a website with Lovable.\n↓↓↓\n\nIn ~3h, I built a fully responsive v0 website for HyperGrowth Partners using Lovable.\n\nIt's not finished. It's far from perfect. But it kinda works.\n\nAnd it was my first vibe coding experience.\n\nYeah, it was a vibe — but here's what I've learned.\n\n↓↓↓\n\n1) Start with a big fat prompt\n- Long, structured prompts are better than one-liners\n- Define role, task sequences, n. of pages, components per pages\n- I'll paste mine below\n\n2) Go from wide to narrow\n- It's tempting to nail the details, but force yourself to go wide first\n- Nail the n. of pages, then site-wide elements (navbar/footer/links)\n- Then components per page, then UI per component\n\n3) Use component libraries\n- I used https://lnkd.in/diiTWunz to get pre-made UI components\n- I love 21st dev because you just copy/paste prompts to make the component in Lovable\n\n4) Use other websites screenshots as visual references\n- A picture says more than 1000 words, even to LLMs\n- Instead of writing/whispering to Lovable, paste a screenshot of a UI you like\n- It's impressive how detailed Lovable is in replicating the screenshot\n\n5) Hover over components to look for UI glitches\n- Sometimes Lovable can't tell what's broken in the UI\n- Hover over each component and use \"Edit\" to edit directly\n\n6) Paste tables from spreadsheets or Notion as CMS\n- Just paste tables into the chat and Lovable creates structured CMSs\n- It even adds filters and metadata\n\n7) Upload logos, avatars, and slide decks\n- Just upload logos and avatars, and it allocates intelligently where needed\n- This really calls for a Brandfetch integration with natural language search\n- Also, upload slide decks to import messaging and copy guidelines\n\n8) Restart \u003E Getting stuck\n- If you get stuck for some reason, just start a new project\n- You could just feed your previous version and Lovable will restart from there\n\n9) 1 credit = 1 message\n- Club together multiple tasks in one message to save credits $$$\n- Their new agent mode should curb this but still worth noting\n- Again, shows how clarity is important when working with machines :)\n\n10) Use \"Chat\" to save credits while still getting stuff done\n- Select \"Chat\" button to chat with Lovable without making edits to your project\n- Ask about SEO, back-end, and more\n\nBONUS: don't forget there's a life out there!\n- It's really lovable to build in Lovable, but also kinda addictive (even the first time)\n- And as much as the founders love to hear this, get a break after few hours\n\n__\n\nThat's a wrap!\n\nOnto more vibe coding now.\n\nWhat's been your biggest learning and challenges vibe coding?",
