      "Content refresh is a game changer.\nHere’s how Webflow scales it effortlessly ↓↓↓\n\nWebflow has 44000+ articles on his site. At this scale, keeping content fresh becomes a massive task. The pressure mounts when new AI tools create more content than teams can handle. \n\nSEO teams face a bottleneck. Each refresh takes hours. \n- Keyword research\n- Competitor analysis\n- Writing and reviews\n- Manual interlinking \n- CMS management\n- ...\n\nThe result? About 40 articles a year. \n\nThis limits growth and leaves opportunities on the table. \n\nIntelligent automation is the answer. Webflow achieved this with AirOps. \n\nThey transformed their content refresh process. Now, updates happen in minutes, not months. \n\n- Automatic prioritization\n- Multi-modal refresh and enrichments\n- One-click updates\n- Human-in-the-loop\n- Native CMS publishing\n\nThis new model scales quality updates. It keeps brand voice intact. The result is a significant traffic boost in days.\n\n- 5X times faster refresh\n- Boost traffic by 40%\n\n__\n\nI sat with Josh Grant — Webflow VP Growth — to unpack their workflow and content refresh strategy.\n\nVisit HyperGrowth Partners's Substack to learn more!\n\nOr comment below/DM me and I'll share the link directly with you.",
