      "Most LinkedIn tools make it easy to create more posts.\nBut these days, volume won't get you far to grow your audience.\n\nSo when anyone can spin up 20 drafts in seconds, what sets you apart?\nI believe you need a closed-loop system to stand out\n\nResearch → Writing → Scheduling → Engagement → Measurement\n\nSo you can:\n- Research the tastemakers in your niche\n- Inject your unique POV and messaging\n- Drive the conversation both when creating and engaging\n- And have each post feeding the next one\n\nThat’s Taplio's bet.\n\nInstead of cobbling together Favikon, Notion, Google Sheets, and Buffer, you can build a pretty-streamlined content ops loop in one pane of glass.\n\nAnd as a solo marketer who needs to ghostwrite for multiple founders — while doing your own personal branding — this data and process integration can become a real multiplier.\n\nTaplio approach works because it helps you combine:\n\n1) Powerful data: top accounts, posts for your topics, and formats, but also best scheduling times based on your geo\n\n2) Workflow integration: run your research, creation, engagement, distribution, and measurement in one platform (even collaboration with your own clients!)\n\n3) Customization: AI speeds up the boring parts, while staying true to your own voice and topics.\n\nIn my latest newsletter deep dive, I've written how Taplio can keep your entire LinkedIn lifecycle humming.\n\nInside you’ll find how to:\n- Turn doom-scrolling into structured research with live swipe files\n- Ground their AI in your brand voice so “garbage in, garbage out” never happens\n- Organize your drafts with a kanban board and scheduler that replaces rogue docs and scattered feedback\n- Engage with the right comments before they go cold\n- Learn from which post link to the best results\n\nI've also included my personal wishlist features I'd love to see on Taplio.\nRead the full piece below.\n\nDM me and I'll send you the full deep dive.",
