      "We see the most complex AI workflows on LinkedIn.\nBut we often forget that the simplest AI use cases are the most effective.\n\nOne of the biggest rules of AI?\n\nGarbage in = garbage out.\n\nMeaning — without grounding the AI in proper context, it won't give you good output.\n\nTo overcome this, you must turn to prompt engineering.\n\nAnd that's what I do — creating structured prompts grounding the AI into things like\n- The overarching goal of the output\n- The specific audience the output is targeting\n- Style and tone of voice constraints\n\nAnd I customize each variable of these prompts for each of my 5-6 clients I manage.\n\nBut I ended up doing lots of manual context gathering and copy paste between prompts to ensure each is air-tight.\n\nBut no more.\n\n___\n\n↓↓↓\n\nIntroducing: Genesys Brand Kit Generator\n\nJust insert the URL of your company.\n\nAnd you'll get a structured brand kit complete of:\n\n- Brand overview & mission\n- Product overview, capabilities, and benefits\n- ICP\n- Competitors \n- Product differentiators\n- Brand narrative\n- Social proof\n- Writing style & rules\n- Top content\n- Brand objection & responses\n- CTA\n\nWhat do you do with it?\n\n1) Add it as *Instructions* to your GPT folders or LLM chats to ground the AI with context\n(I use a dedicated project folder for each of my clients with these kits)\n\n2) If you're using AirOps, they have a dedicated brand kit for the same use case \n(they've been my inspo for this GPT 🤝)\n\n3) You can now have leaner prompts and streamline your workflows faster\n(without variables like audience, style, tone)\n\n___\n\nWant to try it out for your company or clients?\n\nLike + Connect + Comment \"𝗕𝗿𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗸𝗶𝘁\" and I'll DM it to you personally (no automation).\n\nRepost this to get priority access.\n(𝗠𝗮𝗸𝗲 𝘀𝘂𝗿𝗲 𝘄𝗲'𝗿𝗲 𝗰𝗼𝗻𝗻𝗲𝗰𝘁𝗲𝗱 𝘀𝗼 𝗜 𝗰𝗮𝗻 𝘀𝗵𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗹𝗶𝗻𝗸).\n\n___\n\nPS. I'll be releasing one custom GPTs every week for at least the next 5-6 weeks. Subscribe to my newsletter “newsletter dot genesysgrowth dot com” to get priority access ;)",
