    postContent:
      "This week marked 3 years as a solopreneur at Genesys.\nIt's been a rollercoaster, but I'm loving it  ↓↓↓\n\nTHE BACKSTORY\n\nMay 2022\n- Got fired from OnDeck (ODF) after only 4 months (layoffs season)\n- Lost 80% of my net worth in the crypto bubble burst (lol)\n- Almost break up with my now fiancé\n\nEverything happened in one, intense week BUT:\n- I knew I didn't want to get another FTE\n- Had done 1-2 consulting gigs before\n- Had enough experience to try my luck\n\nSo I refreshed my LinkedIn, and put myself out there.\n(While started doing couple therapy lol)\n\nThings took a rapid twist:\n- Found my first client from the ODF portal (ironic)\n- Then another one came from a uni friend\n- All of a sudden, I was floating\n\nAnd so it began.\n\n__\n\nY1 strategy:\n• Positioning: generalist marketer\n• Target: any tech startup\n• Channels: personal network\n• Model: retainer by hours\n• Goal: keep floating\n\nEOY '22 (7 mos in):\n- Clients: ~3/mo (started writing HyperGrowth Partners NL)\n- Days worked: ~14/mo\n- Revenue: 110% of my prev. job salary\n\nThings to work on:\n→ Get to \"at capacity\"\n→ Get better, more known clients (++ social proof)\n→ Work with clients who value quality work\n\n___\n\nY2 strategy\n• Positioning: generalist, B2B SaaS only\n• Target: seed to Series As\n• Channels: personal network\n• Model: retainer by deliverables\n• Goal: go upmarket (Series A)\n\nEOY '23 (per quarter):\n- Clients: ~5/m (landed first Series A SpotDraft!)\n- Days worked: ~17/mo\n- Revenue: 178% YoY\n\nThings to work on:\n→ Niche down positioning/target\n→ Keep at it with content, start posting on LinkedIn\n→ Let go of non-fit clients\n\n__\n\nY3 strategy\n• Positioning: B2B SaaS product/content marketer\n• Target: Series A-B (some seed)\n• Channels: personal network, LinkedIn\n• Model: retainer by deliverables\n• Goal: go upmarket, grow brand/content\n\nEOY '24 (per quarter):\n- Clients: ~6/mo (Owner.com, Ahrefs, Toast, AirOps, Ethena, Common Room)\n- Days worked: ~18/mo\n- Revenue: 134% YoY\n\nThings to work on:\n→ Automate, streamline, and productize\n→ Consistency with content/social proof\n→ Say 'no' more (hardest part)\n→ More strategic collabs, content, partnerships (eg. GTM Engineer School)\n\n___\n\nWHAT KEEPS ME GOING?\n\nI don't need/want to:\n- \"dominate the market\"\n- get to $$XXM ARR\n- be the best at X\n\nWhat I care about is:\n→ Financial freedom: maintain or improve my lifestyle\n→ Location freedom: work from where I want\n→ Time freedom: retain leverage on my calendar, choose who to work with\n→ Fulfilment: do something I enjoy, keep learning, and feel alive\n→ Optionality: own my choices, and be able to change them\n→ Equity: build my own, not someone else's\n\n__\n\nWithout this set up, it'd have been much harder to:\n- Take ~40 days off p/y\n- Work from Tokyo or Rome 1-2 months p/y \n- Quality time with my 101 yo grandpa\n- Spend her bdays with my Mom\n- Celebrate my old man's retirement in Patagonia\n\nThis post is to say: I'm damn grateful!\n⤷ And if I made it this far, you can do it too!",
