    postContent:
      "Ever have that moment when your job and secret passion collide? 👀\nThat's basically my origin story. And why I’m so excited to announce my next venture. But first, the story that changed it all:\n\nIn my first AE role, we sold so much of the product that we had to FREEZE sales. It was during that time that the company asked me to put my engineering skills to the mix.\n\n“Hey Jorge, while we can’t sell the product, maybe you can look for ways to improve our operations?”\n\nI had to start with a list of things that I knew were taking too much time:\n- Manual prospecting\n- Finding the right contacts + email addresses\n- How to best present the tool in a way that made sense to our potential clients\n\nMy industrial engineering background taught me one critical thing: I was drowning in the WRONG work. So much time spent on repetitive prospecting tasks when I should've been focusing on actual conversations and getting in front of people that could buy.\n\nThe engineer in me couldn’t take it. So I started to work on these systems:\n- Pre-built and customized demos that WOWed our customers\n- Initial “reasearch” cold call strategy to get information on possible tools to integrate with and pain points\n- Scraping public business websites and databases and tying that data back to our CRM\n\nI was doing GTM Engineering before it was a thing.\n\nAfter the 3 month sales freeze, we were closing deals in half the time and our close rates increased 2.4x.\n\nFast forward to my next 3 sales roles, and all were having similar problems. Most didn’t have systems in place that allowed sales to do what they do best: talk to customers.\n\nThe lightbulb moment? Starting to play with Clay (not the stuff that makes your hands dirty).\n\nI got a freelance opportunity. Then got referred to others. Pretty soon I was making as much as my FT role. And with my wife being pregnant, I realized I could:\n- Do what I genuinely loved\n- Work remotely to be present for my new baby\n- Make more money serving sales teams the best way I know how\n\nThe best business ideas aren't fancy innovations, they're solutions to the problems you personally lived through.\n\nAnd that’s why today I’m so excited to announce The GTM Engineering Company. To help sales teams create scalable outbound engines that break through the noise and drive revenue.\n\nI’ve got 2 spots opening up in July, DM me if you want to learn more. Check out my new website: https://lnkd.in/eqwez-ra",
