      "Steal this decision matrix (vibe coded by yours truly) that determines the level of automation to use in your outreach. Here's the 7-step plan to operationalize it: \n\n1. Figure out your ICP (what makes a great company). Enrich data and 'tier' your accounts (eg: High-Fit, Medium-Fit, Low-Fit). AI is great at this research. \n\n2. Bucket titles into two categories: Decision Maker (aka \"above-the-line\") or Individual Contributor (aka \"below-the-line\"). AI is very good at doing this at scale. \n\n3. Come up with a list of the top signals for your business. Use AI to brainstorm the top 20 signals for *your* business (the more specific/niche, the better). \n\n4. Capture these signals across data sources and customized AI agents/workflows. \n\n5. Operationalize these 'decision frameworks' in something like Clay or n8n, to push automated outreach or put in front of reps in Slack, CRM, or SEP.  This image is basically a Clay table. \n\n6. Have AI generate copy and scripts based on the company, person and signal. \n\n7. Keep iterating over time. As your market (inevitably) evolves, your GTM motion should evolve. \n\nPS - For step # 3, drop your website below and I'll share some ideas on signals you should use, based on a prompt/output I've been working on.",
