      "AI is incredibly good at building custom, foundational datasets in your CRM. The stuff your best reps are doing manually, can now be done at-scale (with AI agents/workflows). It's something that I didn't realize was possible until I started doing it for customers this year. \n\nNow, when people come to me to get help with modern Pipe Gen (plays, signal-based selling/automated outbound, Clay and AI workflows), I almost always suggest that we build the foundational dataset first - in their CRM.\n\nSo, I'm testing out a new service:\n\nFoundational Data, enabled by AI.\n\nI'm still working out the details so,\nI want feedback. \n\nSignals, automation and AI are great (really great).\nThey're the obvious future GTM playbook.\nBut, they don't work nearly as well if your foundational data is not dialed first. \n\nThis foundational data layer (in your CRM) also helps with other GTM workflows downstream, like: \n\n- Territory planning (cutting books of business)\n- Lead routing \n- Account scoring \n- Persona reporting \n- Data rooms for investor/board decks \n- (Deep) account research for AEs/AMs\n- NRR cohorting \n- Setting up manual vs. semi-automated vs fully-automated workflows \n- Churn prevention \n- Automated signal scanning \n- Clay workflows \n- Competitor analysis \n- Coaching around consistency \n- And so much more\n\nAI and automation are magic. \nBut they're only as good as the foundational data layer they're built on. \n\nThe good news is: AI can be used to build a great foundational data layer (meta, I know). \n\nComment below (or DM me) if you're interested in learning more about this service.",
