      "This was my favorite slide from the presentations at our Spheres conference.\n\nIt’s Charles Eames’ conceptual visualization of their design philosophy, illustrating how successful design emerges at the intersection of three key domains: \n\n- The Design Office: representing the designer’s capabilities, tools, and creative processes\n\n- The Client: encompassing the specific needs, goals, and constraints of those commissioning the work\n\n- Society as a Whole: reflecting broader cultural, ethical, and social considerations\n\nEames emphasized that the most effective and meaningful design occurs where these three areas overlap, where the designer can work with “conviction and enthusiasm”.\n\nThe diagram itself is intentionally abstract and “wiggly,” capturing the non-linear and often messy nature of the design process.\n\nI love a visualization of thought process - have you seen other great ones?",
