    type: "Image",
    postContent:
      'On Friday, I hosted a dinner with a group of CROs and GTM executives from fast-growing B2B startups. These are people who’ve scaled teams into the hundreds\n\nPeople drove for hours to be there\n\nWhat started as polite networking turned into one of the most honest conversations I’ve ever had about what it really takes to scale\n\nHere are the takeaways that hit the hardest\n\n1. Partnerships\n\nEveryone agreed that partnerships are hit-or-miss.\nROI is inconsistent. Timelines are unpredictable.\n\nBut when you find the right partner and go deep with full integration?\nIt becomes your most valuable growth channel.\n\nThe key? Staying in the game long after others give up.\n\n2. The Hidden Cost of Hiring the Wrong Exec\n\n- Tactical gaps. \n- Board referrals gone wrong. \n- Cultural breakdowns.\n\nOne company had fired 5x more people than they currently employ, because they refuse to compromise on culture fit\n\nAs one CRO put it: "Fire fast or watch your culture die slow."\n\nAnother exec shared this hiring litmus test:\n“If I called them at 2AM on a Sunday with an urgent issue, would they pick up, or wait for Monday?”\n\nExtreme? Maybe.\nEffective at finding people who truly want it? Absolutely.\n\nMy biggest takeaway was that:\n\n- GTM candidates are pros at selling themselves.\n- They’ll tell you exactly what you want to hear.\n\nThe only way to cut through the pitch?\nTry carrying out anonymous reference checks\n\nShout out to everyone who came through\n\nMarcus Mares, Mugais Jahangir, Patrick Lee, Maria Novikova, Danny Khukalenko, Olivier Thibault, Bobby Green, Saif Iqbal, Ajax W.',
