      '8 founders. $1B+ in revenue and funding. One breakfast table.\n\nYesterday, I hosted a private breakfast with some of the most impressive founders in tech, quietly building 8- and 9-figure companies while staying heads-down and mission-focused.\n\nIn the room we had:\n– The founder of Ipsy ($250M+ revenue, 1000+ employees)\n– CEO from HelloFresh (pet food division)\n– Founders of Boast AI, Tri Carter, and more…\n\nCollectively, these founders have built or raised over $1B+.\n\nAnd yet, you’d never guess it from how grounded the room felt.\n\nIt was part of Toronto Tech Week, a week packed with big panels, big names, and even bigger energy.\n\nBut honestly? This tiny breakfast might’ve been the most powerful part of the week.\n\nHere’s what stood out from our conversation:\n\n1. Trust is the new sales funnel.\n2. Fundraising ≠ Business Building.\n3. LinkedIn content has become essential for B2B sales\n4. Small, closed-door conversations \u003E Big panels with investors\n\nWhat hit me most?\n\nThere’s been a total mindset shift in the last few years.\n\n2022: “Why would I, as a CEO, waste time posting content?”\n2024: "I\'m a CEO, how do I build trust with my audience at scale?"\n\nEvery founder is now thinking about content strategy. \n\nPersonal brand isn’t fluff anymore, it’s a core part of your go-to-market.\n\nWant to join our next private roundtable?\n\nComment below with the number that best describes you:\n\n1. Seed & Series A Stage Founders ($3M+ raised/revenue)\n2. Series A–D Stage Founders ($20M+ raised/revenue)\n3. 7 & 8 Figure Agency Owners ($5M+ revenue)\n4. GTM Execs (CEOs, CROs, CMOs, VPs of Sales/Marketing)\n5. VCs (GPs & Partners)\n\nShout out to Laurent Guillemain, Justin Herlick, Levi Goertz, John Than, Carlos Coelho, MBA, Andy Keith, Marcelo Camberos for attending.',
