      "Last night, we had nearly 1,000 RSVPs, but only 100 of the top CMOs, marketing leaders and founders made it through the doors.\n\nI co-hosted a fully booked AI Marketing Panel alongside:\n\n- Laura Pearce (Head of Marketing, Google Canada)\n- Vik Kandeth & Brandon Langevin (VPs & Directors at Stack Adapt)\n- Livia Han (Founding Growth Lead at Tofu)\n\nThe theme?\n\n“Doing More with Less: Marketing in the Age of AI.”\n\nThe big question on everyone’s mind:\n\n“Is AI coming for my marketing job?”\n\nAnd here’s the truth we unpacked:\nAI won’t replace great marketers.\n\nBut marketers who use AI will replace those who don’t.\n\nLaura said it best: “Great people can’t be replaced by great tools.”\n\nEven though Google is leading the charge with Gemini and their AI video models, they're doubling down on HUMAN expertise.\n\nEvery executive in that room (from $1B+ companies like Stack Adapt to trillion-dollar enterprises like Google & SAP) said the same thing:\n\nThey're not looking to cut marketing teams.\nThey're looking to hire marketers who can 10x their output with AI.\n\nHuge shoutout to everyone who pulled up.\n\nWhat’s your take, is AI going to take over our marketing jobs?",
