    postContent:
      "Just wrapped up a private dinner with 5 top go-to-market executives at companies with a combined $500B+ in annual revenue, and we had a brutally honest conversation about what's broken in startup communities:\n\nMost have become way too transactional.\n\nEvent hosts are selling tickets, pushing massive sponsorship slots, promoting their coaching programs at every turn.\n\nIt's obvious they're commercializing relationships instead of building genuine community.\n\nThe problem with this approach:\n\n- Attendees keep their guard up the entire time\n- Real insights get buried under sales pitches\n- People network to GET something, not GIVE something\n- Short-term monetization kills long-term trust\n\nWhich is why we flipped the script:\n\nWe cover dinner. No pitches allowed. No hidden agendas.\n\nJust genuine executives sharing real strategies, real challenges, real wins.\n\nThe result?\nThese leaders opened up about things they'd never share at a \"networking event\":\n\n- When to actually hire your first RevOps person (hint: earlier than you think)\n- Why most GTM strategies fail in execution\n- The side businesses and passion projects they're all building\n- Unfiltered takes on the state of tech and business policies\n\nHere's what I've learned about community building:\n\nYou can't be thinking short-term when it comes to relationships.\n\nYes, I'm a business person. I care about ROI.\n\nBut when you approach community with an abundance mindset. Give first, add value, play the long game, that's when magic happens.\n\nYou never know who will be the next Mark Zuckerberg or Satya Nadella at your table.\n\nMore intimate dinners coming soon\n\nWant to join our next private roundtable?\n\nComment below with the number that best describes you:\n\n1. Seed & Series A Stage Founders ($3M+ raised/revenue)\n2. Series A–D Stage Founders ($20M+ raised/revenue)\n3. 7 & 8 Figure Agency Owners ($5M+ revenue)\n4. GTM Execs (CEOs, CROs, CMOs, VPs of Sales/Marketing)\n5. VCs (GPs & Partners)\n\nBig thanks to Grace Lee Daniel Eskin, CPA, CFBM Mike Thibodeau Pratyaksha Yadav Hilary G. Mustansir Bundiwala for attending.",
