    postContent:
      "Most founders are completely confused about why their startup isn’t growing.\n\nThey blame everything except the real problem.\n\nI’ve spoken to hundreds of struggling founders, and they all say the same things:\n\n→ “Our website doesn’t look professional enough”\n→ “Our branding isn’t on point”\n→ “The product needs more features”\n→ “We need a better sales team”\n\nHere’s the brutal truth: You’re focused on the wrong sh*t.\n\n99% of the time, when I dig deeper, it’s not:\n\n- A product problem\n- A branding problem\n- A website problem\n\nIt’s a TOP OF FUNNEL problem.\n\nYou could have:\n\n- The most beautiful website in your industry\n- A brand identity that belongs in a museum\n- A product your early users love\n\nBut if nobody knows you exist?\nYou’re dead in the water.\n\nIf you can't generate attention, interest, and desire, no one will ever get to the point of trying your product, let alone buying it.\n\nHere’s what most founders don’t understand:\n\n→ More attention = more customers\n→ More customers = better data\n→ Better data = better product\n\nTop of funnel is the flywheel.\n\nBut most of you haven’t even started spinning it.\n\nInstead, you throw money at Facebook, LinkedIn, Google ads.\n\nYou can’t scale what you haven’t proven.",
