    postContent:
      "Just wrapped up breakfast with 5 founders ($250M+ raised, $100M+ ARR), where we discovered a common mistake when scaling companies:\n\nVCs often pressure founders to outsource their conviction\n\nPushing playbooks, hires, and strategies that don't fit the company’s unique path\n\nThe old-school SaaS playbook, hire the ex-Amazon VP, bring in the $1B CRO, implement rigid structures is breaking.\n\nWhy?\n\n- Because what worked from $10B–$100B is useless when you’re at $10M ARR.\n- Because the only person with a degree in your business… is YOU!\n\nEvery founder at the table had hit product-market fit by trusting their gut, obsessing over their customers and doubling down on the scrappy insights they earned in the trenches.\n\nThis is the gap:\n\nPlaybooks written in Silicon Valley in 2013 don't apply in an AI-driven market in 2025.\n\nThe shared truths:\n- Execs with $1B+ resumes often can’t ship\n- Trust your guts and understand what your customers want\n- Great companies are built by conviction, not committee\n\nMost powerful insight?\n\nDon’t let boardroom pressure override your founder instinct.\n\nYes, some VC advice may be helpful but your edge comes from what only you know.\n\nThat’s why I host these breakfasts - to share unfiltered truths with people actually building.\n\nMore curated events coming soon in Toronto and SF.\n\nWant to join our next private roundtable or event?\nComment below with the number that best describes you:\n\n1. Seed & Series A Stage Founders ($3M+ raised/revenue)\n2. Series A–D Stage Founders ($20M+ raised/revenue)\n3. 7 & 8 Figure Agency Owners ($5M+ revenue)\n4. GTM Execs (CEOs, CROs, CMOs, VPs of Sales/Marketing)\n5. Panel for Founder-Led Sales (early/growth stage)\n6. Panel for AI x Marketing (founders, marketing managers/leaders)",
