      "Yesterday I spoke with a CMO at a 9-figure company who asked: “How do we turn LinkedIn into a scalable marketing channel?” Here’s the play:\n\n1. The CEO = The Vision Setter\n\nThey’re not there to chase leads\nTheir job is to shape the bigger story:\n\n→ Where the industry is going\n→ What the company stands for\n→ What big bets and product launches are coming next\n\nThe CEO’s role is to set the narrative and get the market talking.\n\n2. The Executives = The Conversion Engines\n\nEach executive owns a specific audience segment\nAnd speaks directly to their pain points:\n\n→ VP of Sales targeting manufacturing shares real-world case studies on boosting factory efficiency\n→ VP of Product shares real user feedback and how it makes their product the best in market\n→ Head of Sales targeting financial services, shares market insights on the state of the financial services market\n\nSame company\nDifferent voices\n\nLaser-focused messages that actually convert.\n\nThe result?\nTotal market domination.\n\nWhen your ideal buyer opens LinkedIn, they see:\n\n- CEO driving the big picture\n- VPs speaking to their specific pain\n- Case studies, playbooks, and POVs across the board\n\nYou become unavoidable.\n\nMost companies have 5–10 execs doing nothing on LinkedIn.\n\nThat’s like owning Ferraris but walking to work.\n\nIf you want to unlock millions in pipeline by activating your executive team, let’s talk.\n\nDrop a comment and I’ll show you the blueprint.",
