      'Everyone’s chasing product-market fit but no one’s talking about the thing that quietly kills your growth before you even get started: Content-Market Fit\n\nThat moment when your content actually resonates with your ideal customer...\nAnd starts driving real demand:\n\n→ Signups\n→ Demos\n→ Pipeline\n\nMost founders skip this step entirely.\n\nThey think: "Let\'s just throw $100K at ads and see what happens."\n\nHere’s what happens: You get really good at burning money.\n\nIf your content doesn’t resonate organically,\nNo amount of paid ads will save you.\n\nYou need to treat your top-of-funnel the same way you treat your product.\n\n→ Run experiments\n→ Watch the data\n→ Test messages, formats, angles\n→ Double down on what works\n\nStart with organic.\n\n→ Build the muscle.\n→ Earn attention.\n→ Figure out what lands.\n\nTHEN, and only then, should you run ads.\n\nBecause if your message is off?\nIf your content falls flat?\n\nPaid media won’t fix it.\nIt’ll just put a spotlight on your broken funnel.',
