      "STOP being overly thankful in your networking and marketing.\n\nIt’s making you look junior.\n\nI keep seeing DMs and posts like:\n\n“Thank you so much for the opportunity to connect! I’m incredibly grateful and truly honored to be in touch with you.”\n\nOr:\n\n“We’re just so thankful for all the support. We really appreciate everyone who checked out our launch!”\n\nHere’s the issue:\n\nWhen you lead with gratitude, you shrink your authority.\n\nYou’re not a fan. You’re a peer.\n\nTry this instead:\n\n→ Shift from thanks to value\nTry this: “Your post on X was insightful, here’s a quick POV you might appreciate.”\nNot “thanks for connecting”\n\n→ Drop the emotional language\nTry this: “Here’s what we’re building and why it matters.”\nNo more “excited,” “grateful,” “honored.”\n\n→ Position yourself as an equal\nYou don’t need to earn a seat at the table\nShow up with insight. \nOpen a door with relevance.\n\n→ Set a tone of forward motion\nTry this: “This post sparked a few ideas; let’s set up 15mins next week.”\nNot: “Would love to maybe connect sometime if you’re open to it…“\n\nGratitude has its place.\n\nBut if every message reads like a thank-you note, you’re playing from behind.\n\nSeriously, appreciate you reading this 😄",
