      "How I'd fill pipeline from scratch if I was the CMO of a $100M ARR business.\n\n(Send this to your CEO)\n\nHere's my plan:\n\n1. Start creating CONSISTENT CONTENT:\n\nWith your entire executive team\n\nBuyers don't buy from brands these days.\n\nThey buy from PEOPLE they trust.\n\nAnd to trust someone,\n\n↳ You need to see their face\n↳ Hear their voice\n↳ Understand their thinking\n\n2. Produce VIDEO content aggressively\n\nText content is great for top-of-funnel\n\nBut video builds trust for middle and bottom funnel.\n\n↳ Have your go-to-market execs visualize your solution\n↳ Have them show up on camera and humanize the solution.\n\n3. Only THEN start running ads\n\nThis is the correct order.\n\nSo many CMOs get this backward.\n\n↳ Don’t spend a dime until you’ve hit content-market fit organically.\n↳ Once you know which content resonates with your ICP\n↳ Then throw fuel on the fire with paid distribution.\n\n4. Host intimate executive dinners\n\nForget fancy booths at trade shows. Instead,\n\n↳ Gather 10-12 people from your ICP\n↳ Host exclusive, intimate dinners.\n\nThese small gatherings create more pipeline than any trade show booth ever will.\n\n5. Meet prospects in person\n\nContent builds the best top-of-funnel at scale\n\nBut B2B enterprise sales still requires face time.\n\n↳ When prospects have already consumed your content online,\n↳ They'll be warmed up and ready to close in person.\n\nThat's it.\n\nFive channels. Five investments. One scalable pipeline.\n\nWhat would you add or change to this plan? Comment below.",
