      "2,000+ comments later… it’s clear: RevOps wants more strategic impact. Here are 6 ways to do it:\n\n\nCONTEXT \n\nLast week, our Strategic RevOps cheat sheet went viral.\n\nSo we recorded an entire podcast episode to go deeper.\n\n(Just search for 'RevOps Lab' in your podcast app)\n\n\n👉 Here are 6 ways to become more strategic:\n\n𝟭. 𝗔𝗻𝗻𝘂𝗮𝗹 𝗣𝗹𝗮𝗻𝗻𝗶𝗻𝗴: 𝗢𝘄𝗻 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗚𝗧𝗠 𝗽𝗹𝗮𝗻\n\nCreate the bottom-up GTM plan.\nMap it against top-down FP&A.\nHighlight the gaps.\n\nThis gives you exposure to every exec, every trade-off, and every strategic bet.\n\n\n𝟮. 𝗢𝗽𝗲𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝗮𝗹𝗶𝘇𝗲 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗽𝗹𝗮𝗻\n\nBreak the annual plan into quarters.\n\nSet up operating cadences.\n\nHold teams accountable by aligning forecasts with actuals.\n\nWeekly, monthly, quarterly.\n\nDon't just report numbers. Steer the ship.\n\n\n𝟯. 𝗚𝗧𝗠 𝗦𝘁𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗲𝗴𝘆: 𝗜𝗻𝗳𝗹𝘂𝗲𝗻𝗰𝗲 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗯𝗶𝗴 𝗯𝗲𝘁𝘀\n\nWhere should we invest? \n\nWhich geo, segment, ICP, or product?\n\nThese decisions involve trade-offs, risk, and high stakes.\n\nRevOps has the data and perspective to shape these conversations.\n\n\n𝟰. 𝗖𝘂𝘀𝘁𝗼𝗺𝗲𝗿 𝗟𝗶𝗳𝗲𝗰𝘆𝗰𝗹𝗲 𝗠𝗮𝗻𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁\n\nPast $10M+ ARR, expansion \u003E acquisition.\n\nFocus on improving onboarding, adoption, expansion, and retention.\n\nScaling revenue lives in the post-sale motion.\n\n\n𝟱. 𝗥𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗻𝘂𝗲 𝗜𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗹𝗹𝗶𝗴𝗲𝗻𝗰𝗲: 𝗠𝗮𝗸𝗲 𝗱𝗮𝘁𝗮 𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝘀𝘂𝗽𝗲𝗿𝗽𝗼𝘄𝗲𝗿\n\nYou own pipeline insights, conversion analysis, and team performance metrics.\n\nPartner with leadership to drive change from insight to action.\n\nFew roles are better positioned to do this than RevOps.\n\n\n𝟲. 𝗙𝗼𝗿𝗲𝗰𝗮𝘀𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴: 𝗙𝗶𝘅 𝘄𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗺𝗼𝘀𝘁 𝘁𝗲𝗮𝗺𝘀 𝗴𝗲𝘁 𝘄𝗿𝗼𝗻𝗴\n\nLet’s be honest:\n\nMost teams suck at forecasting.\n\nRevOps can bring structure, accuracy, and accountability by combining methods and owning the process.\n\n___\n\nWhat else would you add to drive strategic impact?\n\nDrop your comment 👇",
