    postContent:
      "In 2025, the best RevOps teams use AI notetakers. Here's what 99% of them still get WRONG (+ how to fix it):\n\n\nCONTEXT\n\nFull transparency.\n\nI run Weflow (a Gong alternative at 50% the price).\n\nOur team has seen 1,000+ AI notetaker setups.\n\nFrom SMBs to Enterprise.\n\nAnd there's ONE thing that almost all do wrong.\n\n(Which destroys their Salesforce data quality):\n\nThey use separate tools for their AI notetaker (or Conversation Intelligence) and Activity Capture.\n\nThe problem:\n\nBoth create an event record in Salesforce.\n\nThe consequences:\n\n • Duplicate events\n • Messy activity reporting\n • Low trust in data\n • More RevOps admin\n\nInstead, unify both tools to capture:\n\n- emails\n- meetings\n- recordings\n- transcripts\n- attachments\n- AI summaries\n- AI field updates\n...\n\n(Side note: 200+ B2B revenue teams now happily do this with Weflow).\n\n\n👉 Check for these 5 MUST-HAVE capabilities:\n\n𝟭. 𝗢𝗻𝗲 𝘁𝗼𝗼𝗹, 𝗻𝗼 𝗱𝘂𝗽𝗹𝗶𝗰𝗮𝘁𝗲𝘀\n\nIf a meeting is recorded:\n\n- transcripts\n- AI summaries\n- and the calendar event\n\nshould be combined into ONE Salesforce event.\n\nMake sure to have central access permission to all calendars.\n\nThis prevents data gaps and the need for end-user installs.\n\n\n𝟮. 𝗔𝘂𝘁𝗼-𝗰𝗮𝗽𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲 𝗲𝗺𝗮𝗶𝗹𝘀 & 𝗺𝗲𝗲𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴𝘀\n\nThere are many details to capturing 99.9% of activities reliably.\n\nExamples:\n\n • Are activities permanently stored?\n • Are meetings captured if not recorded?\n • Are incoming & outgoing emails captured?\n • Are there manual controls in Outlook/Google?\n • Are activities auto-mapped to the right record?\n • Can you set up multiple configurations (AE, CSMs)?\n\n\n𝟯. 𝗔𝘂𝘁𝗼𝗺𝗮𝘁𝗲𝗱 𝗰𝗼𝗻𝘁𝗮𝗰𝘁 𝗰𝗮𝗽𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲\n\nReps never manually create contacts from calendar events (or email threads).\n\nSo automate it.\n\nDetails that matter:\n\n • Domain exclusions (@gmail.com, @yahoo.com)\n • Email name exclusions (invoice@, billing@)\n • Only create contacts for existing accounts\n • End user controls in Outlook/Google\n\n\n𝟰. 𝗔𝗜 𝗺𝗲𝗲𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘀𝘂𝗺𝗺𝗮𝗿𝗶𝗲𝘀\n\nYour notetaker's meeting summaries should be stored in the event object.\n\nDetails that matter:\n\n• Can you create custom AI summary templates?\n• Can you combine multiple prompts/templates?\n• Can you assign templates to user profiles?\n\n\n𝟱. 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝘂𝘁𝗼-𝗽𝗼𝗽𝘂𝗹𝗮𝘁𝗲𝘀 𝗖𝗥𝗠 𝗳𝗶𝗲𝗹𝗱𝘀\n\nDo you use your notetakers to populate Salesforce fields with AI?\n\nThe best teams do.\n\n↳ Improves CRM data hygiene.\n↳ Drives productivity gains\n↳ Reps love it!\n\nHere are details that matter:\n\n• Which objects can be updated (Opps, Accounts...)\n• Supported field types (Amount, Picklists...)\n• Can admins map fields to AI prompts\n• Can you build a prompt library\n• Can admins adjust AI prompts\n• Are custom objects supported\n\nAnything I missed? Let me know. 👇 \n\n\n____\n𝗣𝗦: 𝗪𝗮𝗻𝘁 𝘁𝗼 𝗰𝗿𝗲𝗮𝘁𝗲 𝗮 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝘃𝗲𝗻 𝗦𝗮𝗹𝗲𝘀𝗳𝗼𝗿𝗰𝗲 𝗱𝗮𝘁𝗮 𝗰𝗮𝗽𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲 𝘀𝗲𝘁𝘂𝗽? \n\nGet our FREE AC & CI Cheat Sheet:\n\n1. Like + comment \"AC+CI\"\n2. Add me on LI (so I can share it)",
