      'Last week, I posted a "Strategic" RevOps cheat sheet that got 2,000+ comments 🤯. Here are 12 key takeaways for tactical vs. strategic RevOps:\n\n___\nBtw, if you want a free copy:\n\n1. Like + comment “Strategy” or “Weflow”\n2. Connect with me on LinkedIn (so I can send it)\n___\n\nLet\'s move on.\n\nBeing tactical vs. strategic is not just a RevOps debate:\n\nIt exists in finance\nIt exists in product\nIt exists in engineering\n\nIt\'s fine to be tactical in the first 5 years of your career.\n\nEmbrace it. \nGo broad, level up.\nGet a lot of stuff done. \n\nBut to become VP or COO, you need to drive strategy.\n\nHere are 12 dimensions you need to shift from tactical to strategic:\n\n𝟭. 𝗣𝗿𝗶𝗺𝗮𝗿𝘆 𝗳𝗼𝗰𝘂𝘀\n\nTactical: Day-to-day execution and operations\nStrategic: Driving long-term GTM alignment & growth\n\n𝟮. 𝗧𝗶𝗺𝗲 𝗵𝗼𝗿𝗶𝘇𝗼𝗻\n\nTactical: Short-term (this week/quarter)\nStrategic: Medium to long-term (next 2-6 quarters)\n\n𝟯. 𝗥𝗼𝗹𝗲 𝗶𝗻 𝗱𝗲𝗰𝗶𝘀𝗶𝗼𝗻-𝗺𝗮𝗸𝗶𝗻𝗴\n\nTactical: Supports decisions through reports\nStrategic: Influences or leads strategic decisions\n\n𝟰. 𝗧𝗼𝗼𝗹 𝘂𝘀𝗮𝗴𝗲\n\nTactical: Tool administrator; reactive to needs\nStrategic: Technology architect; proactive & ROI-driven\n\n𝟱. 𝗗𝗮𝘁𝗮 𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗸\n\nTactical: Pulls reports on request\nStrategic: Builds predictive and diagnostic analytics\n\n𝟲. 𝗖𝗼𝗹𝗹𝗮𝗯𝗼𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻 𝘀𝘁𝘆𝗹𝗲\n\nTactical: Follows orders from sales/marketing\nStrategic: Acts as a strategic partner & cross-functional leader\n\n𝟳. 𝗕𝘂𝘀𝗶𝗻𝗲𝘀𝘀 𝗶𝗺𝗽𝗮𝗰𝘁\n\nTactical: Operational efficiency\nStrategic: Revenue acceleration & margin improvement\n\n𝟴. 𝗧𝘆𝗽𝗶𝗰𝗮𝗹 𝗱𝗲𝗹𝗶𝘃𝗲𝗿𝗮𝗯𝗹𝗲𝘀\n\nTactical:\n- Daily/weekly reports\n- CRM automations\n- Lead routing fixes\n\nStrategic:\n- Strategic board-level dashboards\n- QBR insights\n- Forecast accuracy models\n\n𝟵. 𝗣𝗲𝗿𝗳𝗼𝗿𝗺𝗮𝗻𝗰𝗲 𝗺𝗲𝘁𝗿𝗶𝗰𝘀\n\nTactical:\n- SLA compliance\n- CRM hygiene scores\n- Time to task completion\n\nStrategic:\n- Forecast accuracy\n- CAC/LTV optimization\n- Pipeline coverage & velocity\n\n𝟭𝟬. 𝗟𝗲𝗮𝗱𝗲𝗿𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗽 𝗽𝗲𝗿𝗰𝗲𝗽𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻\n\nTactical: "Fixer" or "operator"\nStrategic: "Strategist" or "peer"\n\n𝟭𝟭. 𝗠𝗶𝗻𝗱𝘀𝗲𝘁\n\nTactical: Execution-driven\nStrategic: Outcome- and impact-driven\n\n𝟭𝟮. 𝗖𝗮𝗿𝗲𝗲𝗿 𝘁𝗿𝗮𝗷𝗲𝗰𝘁𝗼𝗿𝘆\n\nTactical: Operations Manager → Senior Ops\nStrategic: RevOps leader → COO\n\nWhat would you add? 💬👇\n\n__\nPS: We also discussed Strategic RevOps in the latest RevOps Lab episode👇\n\nEP83: Become Strategic in RevOps\n\n\n#revops #gtm',
