      "Every RevOps person I know tells me the same thing: reps won't update Salesforce. Here are 5 things you can do about it with AI:\n\nFor context:\n\nScaling Weflow we've analyzed deal hygiene across 600+ Salesforce instances.\n\nIt's always the same story:\n • No contact roles\n • Missing next steps\n • Email and meetings not synced\n • Poor stage entry/exit criteria compliance\n • Incomplete MEDDPICC fields (SPICED, etc.)\n • ...\n\nI believe RevOps is best equipped to solve it!\n\n\n𝗛𝗲𝗿𝗲 𝗶𝘀 𝘄𝗵𝘆:\n\nWe treat poor deal hygiene as a \"behavior problem\".\n\nAll reps have the ability to update Salesforce. \n\nBut still, they don't do it. They hate it. \n\nThey feel they get nothing back.\n\nWe spend months reminding & training them. \n\nYet, nothing fundamentally changes.\n\nIt's frustrating!\n\nI believe \"updating Salesforce\" is a tech problem.\n\nAnd we in RevOps can solve it the best.\n\nRule-based systems helped a bit.\n\nBut AI unlocks capabilities unmatched before.\n\n\n𝗛𝗲𝗿𝗲 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝟱 𝗲𝘅𝗮𝗺𝗽𝗹𝗲𝘀:\n\n(Weflow does all of this, by the way)\n\n\n𝟭. 𝗔𝗜 𝗳𝗶𝗲𝗹𝗱 𝘂𝗽𝗱𝗮𝘁𝗲𝘀\n\nConnect any Salesforce field across any object to AI prompts to auto-populate those fields from your meeting transcripts or emails.\n\nReps get an email after the meeting to review, adjust, and update those fields.\n\nIt's fast, it's easy.\n\n(Weflow does that, by the way)\n\n\n𝟮. 𝗔𝗜 𝘀𝘂𝗺𝗺𝗮𝗿𝗶𝗲𝘀\n\nAI notetakers write summaries into the description field in the event object in Salesforce.\n\nImportant: Your notetaker should not create a duplicate event in addition to your activity capture solution. \n\nPro tip: Consolidate Conversation Intelligence and Activity Capture to resolve this issue.\n\n\n𝟯. 𝗔𝗜 𝗰𝗮𝗽𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲𝘀 & 𝗺𝗮𝗽𝘀 𝗰𝗼𝗻𝘁𝗮𝗰𝘁𝘀\n\nAI recognizes \"new contacts\" in email threads and calendar events, and automatically adds them to Salesforce.\n\nHint: Use a solution that offers manual controls in Outlook / Gmail for a hybrid approach.\n\n\n𝟰. 𝗔𝗜 𝗱𝗲𝗮𝗹 𝘀𝘂𝗺𝗺𝗮𝗿𝗶𝗲𝘀\n\nAI analyzes your activity, conversation, and CRM data to automatically provide deal summaries and suggest field updates.\n\n\n𝟱. 𝗔𝘂𝘁𝗼𝗺𝗮𝘁𝗲 𝗮𝗰𝘁𝗶𝘃𝗶𝘁𝘆 𝗰𝗮𝗽𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲\n\nAuto-capture and map emails & meetings from Google/Outlook to Salesforce. \n\nHint: Use a tool that provides manual controls in Gmail/ Outlook for higher mapping accuracy.\n\n\n\nPS: I created 3 FREE cheat sheets to help you get better Salesforce data:\n\n1 - AI Notetaker for Salesforce:\nhttps://lnkd.in/e4HznvpK\n\n2 - Salesforce Activity Capture\nhttps://lnkd.in/eBvYpR_8\n\n3 - Salesforce Data Hygiene:\nhttps://lnkd.in/eu3-a76r",
