      "In 2025, there's no excuse for poor Salesforce deal hygiene. Here are 6 things the best RevOps teams do to get it right:\n\nFor context:\n • I scaled Fyber from 0-76M in ARR\n • I've been running GTM teams for 15 years\n • SFDC deal hygiene has ALWAYS been a struggle\n\nHere is the reality:\n 1. Reps hate CRM data entry\n 2. Managers hate reminding them\n 3. RevOps triages tools, processes & humans\n 4. Executives don't trust the metrics & forecast\n\nNobody wins!\n\nAnd the truth is:\n\nTechnology has become so good, there's no excuse anymore.\n\nHere are 6 ways to solve it:\n\n#𝟭 𝗔𝘂𝘁𝗼-𝗰𝗮𝗽𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲 𝗖𝗥𝗠 𝗳𝗶𝗲𝗹𝗱𝘀 (𝗹𝗶𝗸𝗲 𝗠𝗘𝗗𝗗𝗜𝗖, 𝗻𝗲𝘅𝘁 𝘀𝘁𝗲𝗽𝘀)\n\nKey CRM fields are often empty or miss details.\n\nFix:\n 1. Record & transcribe calls\n 2. Map CRM fields to AI prompts\n 3. Populate text, multi-select, dropdown fields\n 4. Reps should only review, adjust, and confirm\n\nTools:\n • Weflow\n • Attention\n • Gong\n\n#𝟮 𝗠𝗲𝗲𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗻𝗼𝘁𝗲𝘀 𝗼𝗻 𝗮𝘂𝘁𝗼-𝗽𝗶𝗹𝗼𝘁\n\nReps should focus on the conversation, not take notes.\n\nFix:\n 1. Record & transcribe the meeting\n 2. AI summarizes the conversation\n 3. AI updates the note (in ONE event object)\n\nTools: see above.\n\nPS: The best tools allow admins to create AI summary templates for different user profiles. \n\nExamples:\n- SPICED for AEs\n- Account health indicators for CS\n\n#𝟯 𝗔𝘂𝘁𝗼-𝗰𝗮𝗽𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲 𝗲𝗺𝗮𝗶𝗹𝘀 & 𝗺𝗲𝗲𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴𝘀\n\nIt's table stakes.\n\nYet, many teams don't do it (reliably).\n\nFix:\n 1. Install an activity capture app\n 2. Configure your setup & enroll users centrally\n 3. Automatically capture emails & meetings\n 4. Provide manual controls in Outlook/Google\n\nTools:\n • Weflow\n • Revenue Grid\n • Cirrus Insights\n\n#𝟰 𝗔𝘂𝘁𝗼𝗺𝗮𝘁𝗲 𝗰𝗼𝗻𝘁𝗮𝗰𝘁 𝗰𝗮𝗽𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲\n\nMulti-threading is more important than ever - but reps hardly ever add contacts to Salesforce.\n\nEspecially those contacts that are added to email threads or customer meetings later on.\n\nThis means: \n- No visibility into the buying committee\n- Wrong multi-threading metrics\n\nFix:\nIdeally, your activity capture solution covers this (see above).\n\n#𝟱 𝗠𝗮𝗸𝗲 𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗴𝗲 𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗿𝘆/𝗲𝘅𝗶𝘁 𝗰𝗿𝗶𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗶𝗮 𝗲𝗮𝘀𝘆 𝘁𝗼 𝗳𝗼𝗹𝗹𝗼𝘄\n\nDocumenting entry/exit criteria is \"easy\".\n\nHaving reps adopt them is hard.\n\nFix\n 1. Define stage entry/exit criteria\n 2. Document & train the team - again & again\n 3. Use auto-field updates to populate relevant fields\n 4. Implement page layouts & paths for compliance\n\nTools:\n • CRM (SFDC, Hubspot,...)\n • AI notetaker with AI field updates (see above)\n\n#𝟲 𝗔𝘂𝘁𝗼𝗺𝗮𝘁𝗲 𝗲𝗻𝗿𝗶𝗰𝗵𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 & 𝗱𝗲𝗱𝘂𝗽𝗹𝗶𝗰𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻 \n\nIt's table stakes, but crucial. \n\nFix:\n 1. Run dedupe jobs monthly \n 2. Use multiple unique identifiers\n 3. Automate the enrichment process\n 4. Review key fields (email, phone, domain)\n\nTools: \n • Clay\n • Apollo\n • ZoomInfo\n\nWhich tools am I missing? 👇",
