      "We teamed up with a VP, RevOps at a $46M ARR company to help solve 6 challenges on forecasting. Here is what we did: \n\nFor context some metrics on last quarter: \n\nPipeline coverage in week 4 was 2.8x.\n\nCoverage dropped to 1.4x in week 8 (- $7.4M).\n\nThey ended the quarter at 82%.\n\n𝗛𝗲𝗿𝗲 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝟲 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝗹𝗹𝗲𝗻𝗴𝗲𝘀 𝘄𝗲 𝗱𝗶𝘀𝗰𝗼𝘃𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗱 (+ 𝗳𝗶𝘅𝗲𝘀):\n\n𝟭. 𝗗𝗲𝗮𝗹 𝗵𝘆𝗴𝗶𝗲𝗻𝗲 𝗶𝗻 𝗦𝗮𝗹𝗲𝘀𝗳𝗼𝗿𝗰𝗲 𝘄𝗮𝘀 𝗽𝗼𝗼𝗿\n- Activity data was missing\n- 62% if MEDDICC fields were empty\n- Next steps fields were mostly empty\n\nAll this required manual data entry that reps tried to avoid as it slowed them down.\n\nFix:\n↳ Automated activity capture (Weflow Activity Capture)\n↳ Automated field updates (Weflow Conversation Intelligence)\n\nPS: Comment „Salesforce Data Capture“ to get our free cheat sheet on the topic.\n\n𝟮. 𝗗𝗲𝗮𝗹𝘀 𝘄𝗲𝗿𝗲 𝗽𝘂𝘀𝗵𝗲𝗱 𝘁𝗼 𝗻𝗲𝘅𝘁 𝗾𝘂𝗮𝗿𝘁𝗲𝗿\n\nBetween week 4 to 8, 23% of deals were pushed to the next quarter. The problem was that manager didn't know which deals were pushed.\n\nFix:\n↳ Added „push count“ to pipeline views\n↳ Added \"pushed deals\" column to roll-up views\n\n𝟯. 𝗦𝘁𝗮𝗹𝗹𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗱𝗲𝗮𝗹𝘀 𝘄𝗲𝗿𝗲 𝗻𝗼𝘁 𝘃𝗶𝘀𝗶𝗯𝗶𝗯𝗹𝗲 \n\nAfter week 6+, 16% of deals were not advancing. \n\nWhy?\n\nAfter automating activity capture, we saw that:\n↳ prospects didn’t reply to emails\n↳ many deals had no next meeting scheduled\n\nFix:\n↳ Added warnings for stalling deals\n↳ Surfaced emails & meetings in pipeline views\n↳ Introduced reassignment rule for stalling deals\n\n𝟰. 𝗗𝗲𝗮𝗹 𝗿𝗲𝘃𝗶𝗲𝘄𝘀 𝘄𝗲𝗿𝗲 𝗶𝗻𝗲𝗳𝗳𝗲𝗰𝘁𝗶𝘃𝗲\n\nManagers used deal reviews to find out if deals are healthy without a framework nor visibility.\n\nWhy?\n\nVisibility into deal health was poor due to:\n↳ missing deal hygiene\n↳ missing MEDDIC framework\n↳ missing warnings, signals, and insights\n\nFix:\n↳ Used MEDDICC data to run deal reviews\n↳ Trained managers on effective deal reviews\n↳ Created views that showcase the right warnings, signals and fields to identify risks easier.\n\n𝟱. 𝗕𝗼𝘁𝘁𝗼𝗺-𝘂𝗽 𝗳𝗼𝗿𝗲𝗰𝗮𝘀𝘁 𝘄𝗮𝘀𝗻'𝘁 𝗱𝗿𝗶𝘃𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝗰𝗰𝗼𝘂𝗻𝘁𝗮𝗯𝗶𝗹𝗶𝘁𝘆\n\nOnly Managers submitted forecast calls.\n\nWhy?\nManager forecasts were tracked in a spreadsheet which didn't scale to have reps submit as well.\n\nFix:\n↳ Asked rep to submit forecast calls\n↳ Introduced deal-by-deal bottom-up forecasting\n↳ Used Deal Intelligence for Manager adjustments\n\n𝟲. 𝗥𝗲𝗹𝗶𝗮𝗻𝗰𝗲 𝗼𝗻 𝘁𝗼𝗼 𝗳𝗲𝘄 𝗳𝗼𝗿𝗲𝗰𝗮𝘀𝘁 𝗺𝗲𝘁𝗵𝗼𝗱𝗼𝗹𝗼𝗴𝗶𝗲𝘀\n\nTeam only replied on Manager and Weighted Forecast\n\nWhy?\n↳ Stage conversation rates were hard coded\n↳ Spreadsheet made rep forecast impossible\n\nFix:\n↳ Added Weflow’s AI forecasting prediction\n↳ Added dynamic weighted forecast\n↳ Added RevOps technical forecast\n\nWhat would you add? 👇\n\n-\nPS: Check out Weflow to automate Salesforce data capture and improve forecasting accuracy.\n\n🆓 Get our free Forecasting Cheat Sheet\n\n↳ Like + comment „forecast“ or „Weflow Revenue AI“\n↳ Add me on LinkedIn (so I can send it to you)",
