      "I spoke to a RevOps Leader at a $42M ARR co who spent six figures on MEDDPICC...but reps weren't using it. Here's what we discussed (+ fixes):\n\nFirst, we analyzed why MEDDPICC adoption was low.\n\nHere is how RevOps explained it nicely:\n\n • Reps feel it's more work\n • Reps say it's not helping them close deals\n • Managers don't enforce it in 1-1s & deal reviews\n • CRO only looks at swing deals where data is good\n\n...and here are the hard numbers:\n\n • 67% of all MEDDPICC fields are empty\n • 28% of populated fields only had 15 words or less\n\n...and here is why they introduced MEDDPICC:\n\n • Win rates were too low\n • Deals often stall in stage\n • Pipeline coverage drops mid-quarter\n • Deal reviews were missing a framework\n • Quota attainment spread widely across the team\n • YoY Growth rates dropped to single digits\n\nNot a good place to be in as a hyper-growth company.\n\nAs you know, there isn't an \"easy\" fix as it's a:\n\n • Change management problem\n • Enablement problem\n • Process problem\n • Tool problem\n\n𝗛𝗲𝗿𝗲 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝟲 𝘀𝘁𝗲𝗽𝘀 𝘄𝗲 𝗱𝗶𝘀𝗰𝘂𝘀𝘀𝗲𝗱 𝘁𝗼 𝗱𝗿𝗶𝘃𝗲 𝗠𝗘𝗗𝗗𝗣𝗜𝗖𝗖 𝗮𝗱𝗼𝗽𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻:\n\n𝟭 - 𝗥𝗲𝗱𝘂𝗰𝗲 𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗸 𝗳𝗼𝗿 𝗿𝗲𝗽𝘀\n\nGoals: \n • Free reps from MEDDPICC data entry\n • Improve MEDDPICC data quality\n\nHow?\nReps adopted Weflow's AI Notetaker to auto-update Salesforce fields. After a meeting, reps get an email to update fields, review populated fields, edit if necessary, and click update!\n\nResults:\n • 1 min instead of 10 min manual data entry.\n • 82% of MEDDPICC fields populated.\n\n𝟮 - 𝗠𝗘𝗗𝗗𝗣𝗜𝗖𝗖-𝗳𝗶𝗿𝘀𝘁 𝗱𝗲𝗮𝗹 𝗿𝗲𝘃𝗶𝗲𝘄𝘀\n\nGoal: Ensure MEDDPICC is used in deal reviews\n\nHow?\nWe created a deal review pipeline view displaying all MEDDPICC fields to ensure reps and managers look at it again and again.\n\nPlus, Enablement trained managers on MEDDPICC-first deal reviews\n\n𝟯 - 𝗦𝗵𝗼𝘄𝗰𝗮𝘀𝗲 𝗠𝗘𝗗𝗗𝗣𝗜𝗖𝗖 𝘀𝘂𝗰𝗰𝗲𝘀𝘀\n\nGoal: Display how MEDDPICC helps to win deals\n\nHow?\n • Analyze win rate of closed-won deals\n • Display difference to non-compliant deals\n • Communicate, communicate, communicate\n\nResult: Reps finally understand why it matters.\n\n𝟰 - 𝗦𝗲𝗹𝗳-𝗰𝗼𝗮𝗰𝗵𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝗴𝗮𝗶𝗻𝘀𝘁 𝗠𝗘𝗗𝗗𝗣𝗜𝗖𝗖\n\nGoal: Level up rep performance\n\nHow?\nWeflow's AI Coaching gives feedback and scores every meeting against MEDDPICC. \n\nPlus, Enablement scheduled group sessions to share learnings on MEDDPICC.\n\nResult:\nTo early to tell tbh.\n\n𝟱 - 𝗧𝗿𝗮𝗶𝗻𝗶𝗻𝗴𝘀\nGoal: Improve MEDDPICC adoption through training\n\nHow?\nIn addition to the group session above, we created a MEDDPICC certificate, which was a mixture of self-coaching, call reviews, and practical training sessions.\n\n𝟲 - 𝗢𝗻𝗯𝗼𝗮𝗿𝗱𝗶𝗻𝗴𝘀\nGoal: Incorporate MEDDPICC into onboarding to reduce ramp time\n\nHow?\n • MEDDPICC handbook\n • Multiple training sessions\n • Library clips to share best practice usage\n\nWant to try Weflow for free? DM me or go to getweflow.com",
