    postContent:
      "Spoke to a VP, RevOps of a $32M ARR company about Salesforce hygiene. Here are the 3 problems she faced (+ how to fix them):\n\nFirst, we audited the Opportunity data in Salesforce.\n\nHere is what we found:\n • 72% had ALL MEDDIC fields empty\n • 63% had inaccurate activities\n • 23% had overdue close dates\n • 46% had no next steps\n\nHere is how the VP described the ripple effects in the organization:\n\n1. Inspecting Opportunity health was impossible\n2. Deal reviews have become interrogations\n3. Managers cannot forecast their territories\n4. Preparing forecasting meetings takes ages\n5. Pipeline coverage evaporates mid-quarter\n6. The CRO is deeply annoyed (rightly so)\n7. Board pressure is rising.\n\nHere are 3 root causes we identified (+ fixes):\n\n1. Siloed transcript data\n\nUsing a 1st gen AI notetaker caused problems:\n • AI summaries not synced to Salesforce\n • Meetings created duplicate events in SFDC\n • No capability to auto-update fields in SFDC\n\nThe fix:\nPiloting Weflow Conversation Intelligence\n\n2. Ineffective activity capture\nActivities were missing and not mapping accurately to Opportunities. \n\nHere is the setup (and the problem):\n • AEs used a Gmail extension to log emails\n • The Gmail extension only logged outgoing emails\n • Low adoption as anual and time-consuming (3-4 clicks/ email)\n • AE constantly needed to re-authentificate\n • So, many didn't bother to log emails anymore\n\nPS: They tried Einstein Activity Capture but stopped using it because of reporting, mapping, and data persistence reasons.\n\nThe fix\n1 - Automating activities capture\n2 - Manual controls in Gmail\n3 - Visibility in deal reviews\n\nCombining automated activity capture with manual controls in Gmail & Google Calendar allowed them to accurately map to Opportunities using Weflow's Activity Capture product.\n\n3. Missing process compliance\n\nThe team was overwhelmed with the Salesforce instance. \n\nThe problems:\n • Unclear what to do in which stage\n • Too many fields\n • No training\n\nThe fix\n1 - Simplify required fields\n\nKeep it to 5-7 must-have fields. Remove nice-to-have fields. Focus on deal-critical information\n\n2 - Entry/ exit criteria\n\nDefine Setup views to enable your middle management to discuss \"non-compliant\" opportunities\n\n3 - Training\nIntroduced regular trainings and improved onboarding process to ensure process compliance.\n\nWhat would you add?",
